So I tried, and here the main modifications (async_log_helper.h:66)

#ifndef _has_no_default_move
   async_msg(async_msg &&other) = default;
   async_msg &operator=(async_msg &&other) = default;
#else
#include <utility>
        async_msg(async_msg &&other)
           : level(other.level)
           , thread_id(other.thread_id)
           , msg_type(other.msg_type)
           , msg_id(other.msg_id)
        {  
        }
        async_msg &operator=(async_msg &&other)
        {
           return *std::move(&other);
        }
#endif


==> Result?
1) Basic examples work, at least this give a hello world feel of your lib.
2) But, the last part of the examples seems buggy: when lauching from command-line, the program hangs until a Ctrl-C kill; and when stepping with Visual Studio, an exception is raised, because program repeatedly fails to open a file.
3) The test suite fails.

Any ideas please?

@gabime defaulted move doesn't work in VS2013 (a.k.a. VS12) so I think this should be re-opened:

    ...\spdlog\details\../details/async_log_helper.h(67): error C2610: 'spdlog::details::async_log_helper::async_msg::async_msg(spdlog::details::async_log_helper::async_msg &&)' : is not a special member function which can be defaulted
    ...\spdlog\details\../details/async_log_helper.h(68): error C2610: 'spdlog::details::async_log_helper::async_msg &spdlog::details::async_log_helper::async_msg::operator =(spdlog::details::async_log_helper::async_msg &&)' : is not a special member function which can be defaulted

Changing the code like this works:

    #if defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER <= 1800
        async_msg(async_msg &&other) SPDLOG_NOEXCEPT
            : level(other.level)
            , time(other.time)
            , thread_id(other.thread_id)
            , txt(move(other.txt))
            , msg_type(other.msg_type)
            , msg_id(other.msg_id)
        {
        }

        async_msg &operator=(async_msg &&other) SPDLOG_NOEXCEPT
        {
            level = other.level;
            time = other.time;
            thread_id = other.thread_id;
            txt = move(other.txt);
            msg_type = other.msg_type;
            msg_id = other.msg_id;
            return *this;
        }
    #else
        async_msg(async_msg &&other) = default;
        async_msg &operator=(async_msg &&other) = default;
    #endif
